SIMPLE: friendship
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Friendship
<hw>Friend"ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>fre⟦oacute⟧ndscipe</ets>. See <er>Friend</er>, and
<er>-ship</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being friends;
friendly relation, or attachment, to a person, or between persons;
affection arising from mutual esteem and good will; friendliness; amity;
good will.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is little <qex>friendship</qex> in the world.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There can be no <qex>friendship</qex> without confidence, and no
confidence without integrity.</q> <rj><qau>Rambler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Preferred by <qex>friendship</qex>, and not chosen by
sufficiency.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Kindly aid; help; assistance,</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some <qex>friendship</qex> will it [a hovel] lend you gainst the
tempest.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Aptness to unite; conformity; affinity; harmony;
correspondence.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those colors . . . have a <qex>friendship</qex> with each
other.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frier</ent>⟦br⟧
